# Meridian — Project Context

React + TypeScript + Vite SPA for ranking physicians by medical school prestige and experience.

## Key paths

- `src/services/doctorApi.ts` — POST `{apiBaseUrl}/v1/rank` (default: https://aireview.com/v1/rank)
- `src/services/promptParser.ts` — parses prompts into `RankRequest`
- `src/config/runtimeConfig.ts` — loads `/config.json` (K8s) then Vite env
- `src/types/api.ts` — API contracts; extend here before backend changes
- `k8s/` — Kubernetes manifests for cloud deployment

## Conventions

- Business logic in `services/` and `hooks/` — no DOM in services (mobile-ready)
- UI in `components/` with CSS modules
- Mock data only when `useMockApi` is true — production calls real API
- Self-hosted fonts via `@fontsource/*` — do not add Google Fonts CDN links
- Extend `RankRequest` for new search filters; keep `version` field for API versioning

## Backend handoff

Read `AGENTS.md` for full API contract. Map snake_case API responses in `doctorApi.ts`. Do not change endpoint path without updating `config.json`, `.env.example`, and K8s ConfigMap.
